rComments:
Overall entertaining professor who cares about content she is teaching. 

Grading on written assignments lacks a clear marking system, and are strictly marked. 
You'll get docked for things not made specific on the assignment.

Overall dirt easy course, with interesting content.
I absolutely loved having her as a prof. Super interesting content and prof. There was no final but regular small assignments or quizzes instead, this was fantastic. 100% would recommend.

Professor Henry is amazing . She provides interesting lectures. She is just awesome. She clearly outlines what is expected of students. I thought PSY3122 was a great class, the content was very interesting. She delivers the material so well. The evaluations are usually a bunch of small assignments and quizzes, no final exam which was very nice!

Lisa Henry is such a great prof. The course is so interesting and she has a very laid back teaching method. You can tell she genuinely cares. We had no final exam and you could've been done the course end of November - there's 3 options for the final project on different dates. Take 3122 for sure and also take 3121 with Erin if you can!!

Lisa Henry is literally the best prof I've ever had. We were evaluated on many quizzes, assignments and tasks but no final exam so that was nice. She's genuine, inclusive and knows what shes talking about. Such a great prof and class!!!

One of the best profs in the psych department. Been lucky enough to take 3 classes with her, she delivers such interesting lectures and course material is so unique. Extremely clear grading criteria, love you LISA!

Really interesting material. The course felt like there were just enough assignments/tests and didn't get overwhelming! Professor Henry makes the assignments interesting and lectures fun - would definitely recommend her course.

Loved this class! It was offered partially asynchronously (about 1/3 of lectures were synchronous meetings because of guest speakers, etc.). Assignments were clear and reflected the content well. The textbook was important for readings and the like, but the pdf is free online. Professor Henry was a great lecturer. Would take another of her courses

Very knowledgeable and easy to listen to! Short weekly assignments were a huge grade booster, posts her lectures if you aren't able to attend and modifies the textbooks so they aren't so expensive for her students which is so helpful. Really nice all around and great if you're looking to take any psych elective. Overall couldn't ask for more!
10/10 So nice and funny. Her assignments were short & sweet, around 250 words per 15% paper. It was interesting and I learnt a lot!

Prof. Henry is so sweet, kind, and caring! She modified her grading scheme to reduce workload for students during the stress of the pandemic, and only gave us one assignment or test per week as evaluations (no midterms or final!) which was SO nice. I learned so much in her class, and she made it so fun! She is an amazing prof and 10/10 recommend :)
Best class and best prof!

Hands down the kindest and prettiest professor Ive ever come across! She is so sweet. Assignments and quizzes were so fair! Its seriously really easy to do well if you just follow her rubrics and study what she tells you too!

The best Prof at Uottawa. If you have an opportunity to take one of her classes, do it! She is so amazing and wants her students to succeed and she will give you every opportunity to do so. The best!!

LOVE her! The course work was very manigable & she clearly care's about her students. Class material is very interesting; Its like the SexEd I never got in HS. She only makes you read the texbook sections you need which I appreaciated. If you watch the videos, take notes, and skim the readings, its an easy A! Also no final. 10/10 would recommend!

Lisa Henry is a great teacher. 2 exams:midterm and final exam. + A project (9 pages) . Amazing personnality, great human being. Relaxing voice. Her class are not that hard if you are truly into it. TAKE THE CLASS!!!
Fantastic prof. Going to her class was well worth having a full day on campus. Her classes are always entertaining and factual and I have 0 complaints whatsoever. Thanks Dr. Henry :)

This was an amazing class and it was all because of Dr. Henry. You have to write a midterm and a final but you have the option to write a paper as well. I appreciate that she cares about the students and I liked the discussions we had (which were on the exam)

Lisa is an amazing proff. Her exams are not that easy, but the way she presents information in class and engages with her class is unmatched. She really cares about her students, and as well as being open to every topic, no matter the subject. At the end of the course she answered anon questions asked by the class, that was fun. Laid back and chill
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She's hands down one of the best profs I've ever had! She cares about her students and goes above and beyond to help. I wish I could take her class all over again... She makes a 3-hour lecture feel shorter than an hour and a half one. She teaches with such passion and is extremely open-minded! She's helped me a lot and it's very appreciated!
Shes just the best. I wish I could take her classes all year! Her exams are straightforward, no surprises and you can tell she truly cares about her students. Love this prof, loved this class!
She is a good teacher but her exams are very hard.

Such a great prof, first prof that ever made a 7-10 feel short. The subject matter is very interesting and she presents in a fun and interactive way that makes it easy to remember. Attendance is mandatory if you want a good grade as group discussions are often relevant to exams. One midterm one final with MC and short answers. HIGHLY RECOMMEND

One of the best profs I've had at uOttawa. Her classes are so engaging, half the class is usually a class discussion (which finds its way to the tests) and the other half is powerpoints. I loved this class, the content was interesting and was presented in an effective way. Definitely have to put in some work but thats pretty standard.

Professor Henry is a great professor. She makes her classes incredibly engaging with a variety of presentations, documentaries, discussions, and guest speakers. She asks questions that encourage open dialogue and conversation, and she is considerate to respond to students questions promptly and thoughtfully. Definitely recommend taking this class.

I really, really wanted to like Lisa Henry. She came in with enthusiasm and a heavy focus on participation, which are the marks of a good prof. However, her in class exercises were unclear and all over the place and she spoke to us like 8th graders. The textbook has everything you need, but the graded group exercises in class force you to stay.

Great professor, by far the best class I've taken in university! Lectures were interesting and engaging, grading was fair, all exam questions straight from the lectures (make sure you type everything). HIGHLY RECOMMEND.
Such a good lecturer and really cares about her students a lot. She's just the best

LISA IS AMAZING!!!!!! First time I've been in a 7-10 and actually actively engaged the entire time without falling asleep. Her tests are so fair and she basically tells you what the short answers will be for human sexual behaviour. Great class discussions... had some pretty good laughs (guy that gets aroused by turning into a blueberry lol)

She gives great lectures, always very interesting and she is very funny. Course is 50% midterm 50% final which is a little risky but if you go to class and take good notes you will do well. Course is interesting and she changes it up between guest lecturers and videos, tends to go by very quickly.

Awesome course! Interesting material and guest lecturers, no exams and multiple easy projects. She goes over everything you need to know during class, there is no textbook and class discussions are interesting. Lisa is awesome! Take her classes!
Lisa Henry is such a gem. She is kind, funny, respectable, and an amazing lecturer. As long as you go to class and take good notes you'll do well.
Perspective is a little controversial in some areas, but overall a very interesting class. You learn a lot and are never bored
Amazing professor and human being. She really cares about her students and makes 3hr lectures go by fast. The exams are no walk in the park, but go to class and do the readings and you'll do fine.

This class was amazing. Your views on sexuality will be changed forever. She is an incredible speaker and it is the first course for me where I was never bored in any lecture. Must go to class and catch almost all of what she says. You will get the multiple choice questions WRONG if you skip class because you will miss important details.
I LOVE HER, HER LECTURES ARE AMAZING, TAKE A CLASS WITH HER. And lets be honest, the subject is pretty darn interesting *wink wink*
Super interesting course in general, the professor just makes it that much better. Fun course, but it was 50/50 so a little intimidating... Other than that, super fun overall!

Really loved this class! Henry is very knowledgeable and explains things clearly. She's very open and easy to approach, cares about her students. She gives a chart before exams with the important information to know which really helped! Only 1 midterm and 1 final and you really have to know your stuff but overall loved this class.

Dr. Henry is one of the best professors i've ever had! Not only is she a great lecturer but she cares about her students! She provides a detailed document of what to focus on for chapter readings to ensure you maximize your study time. Its a midterm and final 50% each but she gives you the option to write a paper! Would recommend her class 100%

Vraiment bonne prof. Elle est claire dans ce que nous devons savoir pour les examens. Elle donne beaucoup d'indices en classe sur ce qui se trouvera sur l'examen. La présence au cours est très importante car tout ce qu'elle dit peut être matière à examen. Possibilité de faire un travail de 30% (je recommande de le faire j'ai eu A+ facilement).

Prof Henry is one the best profs at uOttawa! Amazing person and truly cares about her students. She will give multiple hints for what's going to be on the exam. Her lectures go by super quick for 3 hours. Really great! Definitely recommend!

One of the BEST PROFS ever!! She really wants her students to succeed. She is not one of those profs that tricks her students to bring the class average down. If you show up to every single class and take great notes, you are guaranteed an A (You don't even have to read the text book). The game changer really is how well you take notes!

Her class is whatever but her exams are something else ! She makes you feel like everything will be fine by giving you study guides. She says that majority of students get better grades by writing a 30% paper but she soo tough with the grading that you end up losing points

Lisa is a one of a kind professor. She really wants her students to do well both in the course and in their lives. She's very accepting and so free spirited, it feels less like a university class and more of a liberating experience taking her class. You will look forward to sitting in her class every week.

AMAZING PROF! The class was so interesting and she made it really engaging. Really cares about her students and answer some anonymous questions. Her lectures last till the very end and there's a lot of notes to take down, so be prepared to go turbo on typing. 50/50 midterm and final, fairly fair if you study her discussions and the textbook.

This class and Professor Henry literally changed my life. Take this class with her if you can!! She loves when you participate, and you can tell she cares about her students. Attendance is not mandatory but she will carry out the entire 3 hour lecture off 3 slides sometimes. But all extremely interesting material!! I looked forward to it every week
Amazing lecturer. Super fun class that I would recommend to anyone! The exams are actually tough though, but read the textbooks and listen in class and it is very fair.

You need to read the book, esp if you don't come from a science background. I didn't and found the midterm to be quite difficult but used my knowledge to answer questions and still got a 95. She is truly an amazing person and makes talking about your sexuality feel completely normal. She is inspiring and will make jokes, yet keeps it professional!
She is the best professor at uOttawa I have had. Classes are really engaging and 7-10s go by very quickly. You need to study but she is fair.

I have taken two classes with Mrs Henry so far and I absolutely love her. She is really engaging and funny. Be aware that this class material can be quite boring, however, Lisa has a gift to make dull material very interesting. She truly cares about everyone's success. Be aware that the multiple choice questions on her exams can be very tricky.

Lisa is a great prof! We were given 15 points of our final mark for participation, we had two exams and a paper to write. The exams were fair but relied on notes from both the textbook and class discussions, so class notes are important. The discussions were always interesting and she gave clues for exam questions. Take the class!!!

She is one of the best profs I've ever had! im not even a psychology student and i take her classes because she is amazing! i took interpersonal relationships and her sexuality class. You have to go to class and take really good notes, but her lectures are SUPER interesting and will actually help you out in life! HIGHLY recommend :)

Lisa Henry is one of the most entertaining profs that I have had. Each lecture was a new fascinating topic related to sex. The topics we discuss are actually beneficial for for relationships, love, sex, etc. She cares about her students, and it really shows. I highly recommend her class if you have the opportunity.

By far the best prof I have in psychology. Lisa is enthusiastic, witty, knowledgeable, and relatable. She makes a point of making the classroom a comfortable place for everyone. Gives big hints on exam content. Textbook use is not really necessary to do well if you go to the lectures every week.

Lisa henry is a good prof, but she is a hard tester. Had to get good when you are graded with 50%/50%. Luckily she gives the option for a paper. Overall, nice and caring prof. Very hard material to learn, study, and do good on exams though.

Lisa is such a good teacher i would not hesitate to take another class with her as the teacher. Shes very available for her students. She gives pointers on what will be on the exams. She also does a revision. Shes really dedicated

Simply put, everybody should take this class :) It's so rich in learning!!!! Lisa is great and very passionate! Only things to beware: TAKE NOTES!! the conversations in class are crucial if you are seeking a good grade and YES she is very specific and sometimes her questions are tricked a bit or you must use the exact wording to get full points.

BEST TEACHER EVER AND BEST CLASS EVER! Such interesting classes and you can tell she's very resourceful and always there to answer any questions! Have to go to class to take notes because the discussions in class will be on the exam. She makes the class so interesting! Definitely recommend the prof and the class to everyone!

Her lectures were great. She only used one powerpoint (about 1 to 3 slides per 3 hour lecture) throughout the whole semester so showing up is really important to take notes. Everything she says can be found in the exams, but she points you in the right direction by giving some of the questions before. Overall great prof.
She is the best teacher I never had!!!

She really cares about her students and makes sure they succeed. The things you are graded on are pretty easy to do well on. She really encourages discussion, we watched videos and also had 2 guest lecturers. There are no written tests so no need to memorize anything. Would highly recommend this prof !

Lisa Henry is one of those profs you'll remember for a long time after you graduate. She delivers the course in such a great way that encourages discussion and actually makes you listen and be interested. To succeed, honestly just show up to class, pay attention and take good notes, that alone can guarantee you an 80 !!

She's extremely passionate about human sexuality and you can clearly tell. Her teaching is fun and lectures are really interesting. She even had a custom textbook made so we would pay less and only worry about the content she's teaching specifically! Honestly, this class is great and she's great.
Lisa Henry is incredible. She makes sure classes are comfortable and not at all awkward. She always has a smile on her face and delivers all the material in a wonderfully engaging way.
The best prof I've ever had. The midterm can be difficult as she tests you on very specific details in the textbook, and class discussions. But overall I'd recommend this class to anybody

I LOVED Lisa Henry's class. If you skip class you're not going to do well because it's super important to get lecture notes. The textbook alone won't get you through. That being said, it's refreshing to get a prof who knows her stuff and cares so much about the subject matter. A really lovely lady. Highly recommended and would take her class again.

Lovely professor. Enjoys what she teaches, shows she's knowledgable on the course material by not needing to rely on power points too much. Textbook chapters are important for exams. Class attendance is necessary to get the information she says during lectures. Exams are very long and packed with specifics.

Mrs Henry is a really good prof! She is very passionate, funny and explains the material very clearly. Her exams are fair and she is always ready to answer questions. Overall I loved this class and this prof!

Seeks interaction from students, but has nothing to offer them. She nods upon interesting comments and moves on without elaborating... Also, beware of the night classes... I was surrounded by predjudicial idiots where I felt I was back to high school. Educational content of a first year class with time consuming assignments. Highly disappointed.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'So many papers', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Très bonne prof! Un cours que je recommande! Super intéressant! Je conseille de faire le projet optionnel puisque l'examen final est plus difficile.

She is the sweetest prof ever! Evaluations are either 2 exams worth 50% each or you have an option of writing a paper. Lectures are interesting and she's fun! She really cares about the students and is organized. She tells us clearly what's going to be on the exams and what's not. I'm going to miss her!
Worse class I ever took, she's brutal and tough on assignments. Way more work than any class I've ever gotten and she's very picky on how the work is done.

I took her 3rd year class which was good but take her 4th year class at your own risk. She gives us 5 projects and 2 exams and shes huge on introspection, reflexion, elaborating and readings. If I could without a doubt  I would switch out and take another class
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'So many papers']

rComments: GREAT PROF!! great explanations, interesting classes, lots of info for exams but all in all great time
an excellent prof! I highly recommend :)
MEILLEUR COURS!!la prof est excellente, le cours est captivant! On a rie, on a posé des question!! TOUT est possible et aucune question n'est stupide!
Très bon prof. La moyenne était super élevé pour le cours d'été. Utilise beaucoup le livre mais la lecture se fait bien. Aucun piège à l'examen, très possible d'avoir un 100 dans le cours.

I went out of my way to take this class with her. I've taken other classes with her & if you show up for class & do a quick glance over the readings you can get Bs with out devoting many hours so it's great to take her class if you know you have a time consuming one to compensate for. This does not mean it is easy, just that lectures do their job.

great prof! so passionate about the subject matter and genuinely cares about her students. she gave out her cell phone number the first day so we could get in contact with her if some of the sensitive subject matter bothered us. exams are tough but fair... overall amazing class, would take another taught by her

Really great prof who loves what she's doing. Dont be afraid to ask questions or to suggest discussions. Exams are pretty fair and reflect the contents of the class. Read the textbook, it's important, but also listen when she talks about socially related problems in class. These will be on exams. Overall, really good prof :)

You would have to work hard to fail her class. She is funny, interesting & engaging. If you do miss a class the text has enough in it that you can read that. BUT go to class & get free marks for participation. Maybe if you stayed home drank beer & only looked at the pictures in the text you would fail. I'm taking her other class next year.

She's a great person and prof. Very prepared, understanding, and respectful. Her multiple choice questions are hard - you have to read very carefully. I took both 3102 and 3122 with her and I appreciate the challenge of her teaching style -- I actually felt like I was learning, not just memorizing! :)
She's AWESOME!  Her classes are VERY enjoyable!  I have three hour classes twice a week and I look forward to each lesson!
Lisa is super amazing. Love her! She always cracks jokes and just makes the class a really fun atmosphere. Definitely will be taking classes with her again!

Brilliant prof teaching an awesome course. It was a pleasure to attend her lectures... I really looked forward to her class each week! In my opinion, the exams were very lecture-based... so go to class! Pay attention to class discussions, because they show up on exams. Take a course with her if you can... I would take another in a heartbeat.
very good

Sheâ??s great! Really fun and personable. Exams are always fair. Creates a great class dynamic by inciting class discussions and activities. Iâ??d recommend taking at least one of her classes! Both her Interpersonal Relationships and Human Sexual Behaviour classes are definitely worth taking.

GREAT TEACHER! She has a great personality that really shines through in her teaching. You can tell that she loves her job. She is THE MOST fair grader I have ever had. The exams really reflected what was covered in class/ the imp. parts of the readings. I never missed a class.

Amazing prof and great class. She brings a lot of personal interest and experience in her class content and way of teaching. This is a prof that REALLY cares about her students. Open to talk students outside of class & will go out of her way to make sure students push for an A in her classes. NEED to read textbook for the A though & listen in class
Great prof but the grading is not the best!
Very good prof. Interesting lectures, useful information.

Super prof! I took both Le comportement sexuel humain and Interpersonal relationships with her, and loved both. She is extremely friendly, helpful, and interested in her students. She was absolutely the best experience I have had at university. Go for her!

SUCH an interesting class! The professor is lively, enthusiastic and really knows her material. She creates a great learning atmosphere and really encourages questions and participation. I wish she taught other psychology classes! The best professor I have had so far.

She is an interesting prof who conveys the material  effectively.  You must attend each class since there are both in-class participation marks and short answer questions on exams that pertain only to lecture material. She also assigns an optional essay if you want to make up for bombing the midterm. Overall, an awesome course and prof!

I did not find this professor to be very helpful. Reading expectations are unreasonable for full time students. Very unclear with expectations for the short answer questions (very ambiguous) on the midterm and final exams, taken only from lecture material. Overall very dissapointed with this class as it had the potential to be very interesting.
GREAT professor! Class was very interesting and her tests were fair. Really enjoyed this psy class

This prof was really great..she really knows her stuff and is really always ready to help. Her lectures are fun and if you're not satisfied with your midterm grade, she'll let you do a project so that you get another chance to bring up your average.
AMAZING.  Such a fun class and such an amazing teacher.  Loved it.  Lots of readings, but do-able and interesting!

AMAZING professor!! she guest lectured in my Human Sexual Behaviour class and I thought she was a little dry...but then I had her for this class and I was blown away! She really conveys the subject matter well. She is really funny, is able to laugh at herself, is warm and friendly and has a great rapport with the class.
great teacher, knows her material, good class

Amazing class!  You will not be dissapointed.  The teacher is very friendly and knowledgable... Standard (2) multiple choice exams but she does give those who want to improve their grade an option to write and a term paper. All in all, good teacher.
Too much reading, it's like learn the book by heart for the exams. Very demanding and time consuming!!
Very nice, very clear, A LOT of reading but overall do-able.
No Comments
